pullRequest.body:
We add a new file whose main result is
```lean
theorem LFunction_at_one_ne_zero_of_quadratic {N : ℕ} [NeZero N] {χ : DirichletCharacter ℂ N}
    (hχ : χ ^ 2 = 1) (χ_ne : χ ≠ 1) :
    χ.LFunction 1 ≠ 0 := by
```
which is needed to prove Dirichlet's Theorem on primes in AP.

@loefflerd @CBirkbeck I have restructured the code for the nonvanishing of the L-function of quadratic Dirichlet characters at `s = 1`. In particular (and as envisaged) I have split the main part of the code into properties of the convolution with zeta on the ode side (which might be useful in other contexts) and properties that need the (false) assumption that `L χ 1 = 0`. (Plus some golfing.) Your reviews are welcome!

```suggestion
Our goal is to show that `L(χ, 1) ≠ 0` when `χ` is a (nontrivial) quadratic Dirichlet character.
```
I think maybe here it's better to write `L(χ, 1)` since in docstring at L174 you already write `L(χ, 1)`.

```suggestion
whose L-function vanishes at `s = 1`. -/
```

typo
```suggestion
/-- The arithmetic function associated to a Dirichlet character is multiplicative. -/
```

I suggest
```suggestion
    · simp_rw [← LSeries_zeta_eq_riemannZeta hs, ← natCoe_apply]
```
to avoid the `rfl`

How about
```suggestion
  refine B.F_neg_two.not_gt ?_
```
Can we make this private?
Yes, of course. As bad characters don't exist, this will not be of use outside this file.
This comment will appear in the reference manual, although the declarations it refers to won't, if I'm not mistaken. Maybe change it to a plain comment, `/-` rather than `/-!` ?
Done.

Don't need this as its been opened above. Other than this trivial suggestion it LGTM, sorry I only just got around to looking at this!
